org.openimaj.ml.timeseries

Class TimeSeries<DATA,SINGLE_TYPE,RETURNTYPE extends TimeSeries<DATA,SINGLE_TYPE,RETURNTYPE>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.ml.timeseries.TimeSeries<DATA,SINGLE_TYPE,RETURNTYPE>
  • Type Parameters:
    DATA - the type of the data at each point in time
    SINGLE_TYPE - the type of the an element at a single point in time
    RETURNTYPE - the time series returned by the get
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<IndependentPair<Long,SINGLE_TYPE>>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConcreteTimeSeries, DoubleTimeSeries, TimeSeriesCollection

    public abstract class TimeSeries<DATA,SINGLE_TYPE,RETURNTYPE extends TimeSeries<DATA,SINGLE_TYPE,RETURNTYPE>>
extends Object
implements Iterable<IndependentPair<Long,SINGLE_TYPE>>
    A time series defines data at discrete points in time. The time series has the ability to return data at a specific point in time, return neighbours within some window, closest neighbours or n neighbours before and after a time.

    These values can be used by a TimeSeriesInterpolation to get specific moments in time

    Author:
    Sina Samangooei (ss@ecs.soton.ac.uk)

      • get

        public abstract RETURNTYPE get(long time,
             int nbefore,
             int nafter)
        returns the DATA at a specific point in time and those before and after to the number requested. This method may not return data for the specific requested time if it does not exists. If the time series is completely empty this function may return at an empty array however if at least 1 data point exists and either nbefore and nafter are bigger than 1 then at least 1 datapoint will be returned.

        Data should be returned in order

        Parameters:
        time -
        nbefore -
        nafter -
        Returns:
        all data found with these parameters

      • get

        public abstract RETURNTYPE get(long time,
             long threshbefore,
             long threshafter)
        returns the RETURNTYPE at a specific point in time and those before and after within the specified thresholds. This method may not return data for the specific requested time if it does not exists. Similarly this method may return an empty array if no time data is available within the window specified.

        Data should be returned in order

        Parameters:
        time -
        threshbefore -
        threshafter -
        Returns:
        all data found with these parameters
